Mayer has been romantically involved with [[Jennifer Love Hewitt]],<ref name="contactmusic"/> [[Jessica Simpson]],<ref>{{cite web| title= John Mayer: Jessica Simpson Was "Crazy" in Bed|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/john-mayer-jessica-simpson-was-crazy-2010102 |website= [[Us Weekly]]|access-date=February 10, 2017|date=February 10, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211075049/http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/john-mayer-jessica-simpson-was-crazy-2010102|archive-date= February 11, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Minka Kelly]],<ref name=eastland>{{cite web |last=Eastland |first=Terry |url=http://washingtonexaminer.com/john-mayer-admits-i-was-a-jerk/article/2520919 |title=John Mayer admits: 'I was a jerk' |website=Washington Examiner |date= February 7, 2013 |access-date=August 19, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019092027/http://washingtonexaminer.com/john-mayer-admits-i-was-a-jerk/article/2520919 |archive-date=October 19, 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Jennifer Aniston]],<ref>{{cite news| title= Jennifer Aniston ended relationship with John Mayer because of his Twitter 'obsession' |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/twitter/5038203/Jennifer-Aniston-ended-relationship-with-John-Mayer-because-of-his-Twitter-obsession.html| work= [[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|access-date=February 10, 2017|date=March 23, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170130101353/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/twitter/5038203/Jennifer-Aniston-ended-relationship-with-John-Mayer-because-of-his-Twitter-obsession.html|archive-date=January 30, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Katy Perry]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Nelson|first1=Jeff|title=John Mayer and Katy Perry 'Are Not Back Together,' Says Source – But 'They Will Always Care for Each Other' |url=http://people.com/celebrity/john-mayer-katy-perry-not-back-together-but-will-always-care-for-each-other/| work= People |access-date= February 10, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211081316/http://people.com/celebrity/john-mayer-katy-perry-not-back-together-but-will-always-care-for-each-other/ |archive-date= February 11, 2017| url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Philanthropy ===
In 2002, Mayer created the "Back to You" Fund, a nonprofit organization that focuses on fundraising in the areas of health care, education, the arts and talent development. The foundation auctions exclusive John Mayer items, such as guitar picks, T-shirts and signed CDs. The auctions have been successful, with some tickets selling for more than 17 times their face value.<ref>[http://www.johnmayerauction.com/ The Official John Mayer Auction Site], John Mayer Auction. Retrieved April 23, 2007. {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150131215549/http://www.johnmayerauction.com/ |date=January 31, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.businesshere.com/jmayer_success.htm |title= John Mayer| work= Business Here| access-date= April 23, 2007 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070204233903/http://www.businesshere.com/jmayer_success.htm |archive-date= February 4, 2007 }}</ref>

Mayer participated at the [[Live Earth concert, New York City|East Rutherford, New Jersey]], location of the [[Live Earth]] project, a musical rally to support awareness for [[climate change]] held July 7, 2007.<ref>{{cite news| last= Kilgore| first= Kim |year= 2007|url=http://www.livedaily.com/news/More_cities_added_to_John_Mayers_itinerary-11983.html?t=1 |title= More cities added to John Mayer's itinerary| access-date= May 1, 2007 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090215114914/http://www.livedaily.com/news/More_cities_added_to_John_Mayers_itinerary-11983.html?t=1 |archive-date=February 15, 2009 }}</ref>

Mayer performed at a number of benefits and telethons for charity throughout his career. He has participated in benefits for the [[Elton John AIDS Foundation]].<ref>{{cite journal| last= Adato| first= Allison| display-authors= 1 | date= April 7, 2003| title= Sweet Charity| journal= People | author2= other| volume= 59| number= 13| page= 87}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| last= Gardner| first= Elysa |date= November 4, 2005| title= Celebrities share Elton John's vision| work= USA Today}}</ref> In response to the [[Virginia Tech shooting]], Mayer (along with [[Dave Matthews Band]], [[Phil Vassar]], and [[Nas]]) performed a free concert at Virginia Tech's [[Lane Stadium]] on September 6, 2007.<ref name=vt.edu>{{cite web| publisher= Virginia Tech | date= August 1, 2006|url=http://www.vt.edu/concert/ |title= A Concert For Virginia Tech| website= VT.edu| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070823205848/http://www.vt.edu/concert/ |archive-date= August 23, 2007 }}</ref> followed by an appearance with [[Rob Thomas (musician)|Rob Thomas]] at the Annual Holiday Concert at [[Blythedale Children's Hospital]] in Valhalla that winter.<ref>{{cite news| date= January 7, 2008| title= Fly on the wall| work= Westchester County Business Journal| volume= 47| number= 1| page= 38}}</ref> On December 8, 2007, Mayer hosted the first annual Charity Revue, a tradition he has continued each year. Charities who have benefited from the concerts include [[Toys for Tots]], Inner City Arts and the Los Angeles Mission.<ref name=announce>{{cite web|url=http://www.johnmayer.com/news#4 |title= New Show: 1st Annual Holiday Charity Revue on December 8 at Nokia Theatre LA Live| last= Mayer| first= John | website= JohnMayer.com | publisher= John Mayer| date= November 14, 2007| access-date= December 29, 2007 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071226035537/http://johnmayer.com/news#4| archive-date=December 26, 2007|url-status=dead}}</ref> CDs and DVDs of the first concert were released as ''Where the Light Is'' in July 2008.<ref name="RS where the light is"/><ref name="billboard blackberry"/> Mayer appeared on ''[[Songs for Tibet: The Art of Peace]]'', a celebrity initiative to support [[Tibet]] and the 14th [[Dalai Lama]], [[14th Dalai Lama|Tenzin Gyatso]].<ref>{{cite news| last= Finn| first= Natalie | date= July 22, 2008|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/3342/sting-matthews-mayer-gamer-for-tibet-than-beijing |title= Sting, Matthews, Mayer Gamer for Tibet Than Beijing| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403093555/http://www.eonline.com/news/3342/sting-matthews-mayer-gamer-for-tibet-than-beijing |archive-date= April 3, 2015 | publisher= E!| website= eonline.com| access-date= March 25, 2015}}</ref> Mayer (along with Keith Urban) headlined Tiger Jam 2011 in Las Vegas to help raise around $750,000 for the [[Tiger Woods Foundation]].<ref>{{cite press release| date= May 2, 2011| title= John Mayer, Keith Urban Help Tiger Woods Raise Approximately $750,000 for the Tiger Woods Foundation at the 2011 Tiger Jam| publisher= PRNewswire}}</ref> In January 2013, Mayer participated with [[Zac Brown Band|Zac Brown]] in a benefit concert in [[Bozeman, Montana]] where they raised more than $100,000 for firefighters who battled a wildfire in the summer of 2012 in [[Paradise Valley (Montana)|Paradise Valley]] that destroyed 12,000 acres.<ref name= "benefitconcert"/><ref>{{cite web|last=Benoit|first=Zach|title=Pine Creek fire at 12,000 acres; at least 5 homes lost |url=http://billingsgazette.com/news/state-and-regional/montana/pine-creek-fire-at-acres-at-least-homes-lost/article_d8f8826d-beb7-5fbf-a43b-b76efa505246.html| work=Billings Gazette |access-date=February 18, 2013 |date=August 31, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130704031555/http://billingsgazette.com/news/state-and-regional/montana/pine-creek-fire-at-acres-at-least-homes-lost/article_d8f8826d-beb7-5fbf-a43b-b76efa505246.html|archive-date=July 4, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref>

On March 1, 2019, John Mayer established the Heart and Armor Foundation in support of veterans of war.<ref>{{cite web |title=Heart And Armor Foundation |url=https://www.heartandarmor.org/}}</ref> John has been actively involved in initiatives to help returning veterans for about 12 years.<ref>{{cite magazine |first=Jon |last=Blistein |date=March 1, 2019 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/john-mayer-heart-and-armor-foundation-veterans-802243/ |title=John Mayer Launches Heart and Armor Foundation to Aid Veterans |magazine=Rolling Stone |access-date=May 30, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |agency=Associated Press |date=March 2, 2019 |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/people/2019/03/02/john-mayer-launches-foundation-focused-improving-veterans-health/3039035002/ |title=John Mayer Launches Foundation Focused on Improving the Health Of Veterans |work= USA Today |access-date=May 30, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Sarah |last=Michaud |date=March 1, 2019 |url=https://people.com/music/john-mayer-launches-heart-and-armor-foundation/ |title=John Mayer Launches Heart and Armor Foundation: 'We Can All Do a Better Job of Sharing the Burden' |website=People |access-date=May 30, 2020}}</ref>

===Controversies===
Mayer's relationship with Jessica Simpson coincided with behavior changes that significantly increased his [[tabloid journalism|tabloid]] exposure.<ref name=Playboy/><ref name=Mather/><ref name=ownwordsone>{{cite magazine| date= January 22, 2010 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/john-mayer-in-his-own-words-20100122 | title= John Mayer in His Own Words |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170827131048/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/john-mayer-in-his-own-words-20100122 |archive-date= August 27, 2017| magazine= Rolling Stone| access-date= March 25, 2015}}</ref> Early in his career, he had expressed his resolve to completely avoid drugs, alcohol, [[Nightclub|clubbing]], "[[Red carpet|red-carpet]]" events, dating celebrities, and anything that he felt would detract the focus from his music.<ref name=guthrie>{{cite news| last= Guthrie| first= Blake |date= May 16, 2001|url=https://atlanta.creativeloafing.com/content-159632-Square-pegged |title= Square pegged |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070204095109/http://atlanta.creativeloafing.com/gyrobase/Content?oid=oid%3A4733 |archive-date=February 4, 2007 | work= Creative Loafing| access-date= February 2, 2010}}</ref> In interviews, however, Mayer alluded to experiencing an extreme "anxiety bender" episode in his twenties that motivated him to be less reclusive.<ref name=Hedegaard/><ref name=Mather/> In 2006, he first mentioned that he had begun using [[marijuana]].<ref name="RS06" /> He began making appearances at clubs in Los Angeles and New York City, and Simpson became the first in a string of famous girlfriends, including [[Jennifer Aniston]] and [[Minka Kelly]].<ref name=eastland/> By 2007, his personal life had become regular fodder for the [[Tabloid journalism|gossip media]] and, as a result, Mayer made efforts to control his public image. His online presence increased,{{citation needed|date=March 2015}} he began to stage pranks for the paparazzi,<ref>{{cite journal| last= Garcia| first= Jennifer |date= June 15, 2009 |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20285171,00.html |title= John Mayer Performs, Fakes Pal's Hospital Trip| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150907005741/http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20285171,00.html |archive-date= September 7, 2015 | journal= People| access-date= April 28, 2015}}</ref> and he hosted a segment for the gossip show ''[[TMZ]]''.<ref>{{cite news| date= August 5, 2008|url=https://huffingtonpost.com/2008/07/28/john-mayer-guest-hosts-tm_n_115406.html |title= John Mayer TMZ Video: 'Am I Really A Celebrity?' |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402121122/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2008/07/28/john-mayer-guest-hosts-tm_n_115406.html |archive-date= April 2, 2015 | work= Huffington Post |access-date= March 19, 2015}}</ref>

{{quote box|width=350px|align=right|quote=I abused that ability to express myself, to the point where I was expressing things that weren't true to my thoughts.<ref name=patrickdoyle/>|source=John Mayer, ''Rolling Stone'' interview, January 2013}}
In early 2010, Mayer gave a controversial interview to ''[[Playboy]]'' magazine<ref name=outrage>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1631667/john-mayers-playboy-interview-causes-uproar-online.jhtml|title=John Mayer's Playboy Interview Causes Uproar Online|date=February 10, 2010|publisher=MTV|access-date=July 24, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120629112033/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1631667/john-mayers-playboy-interview-causes-uproar-online.jhtml|archive-date=June 29, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> in which he revealed sexually explicit details about his former girlfriends Jessica Simpson and Jennifer Aniston—calling his relationship with the former "sexual napalm".<ref>{{Cite web|date=2010-04-12|title=John Mayer: Jessica Simpson Is "Sexual Napalm," Jennifer Aniston Hates Twitter|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/john-mayer-jessica-simpso_n_456566|access-date=2021-09-16|website=HuffPost|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Peppin|first=Hayley|title=Jessica Simpson said she was 'floored and embarrassed' after John Mayer called her 'sexual napalm'|url=https://www.insider.com/jessica-simpson-was-floored-after-john-mayer-called-her-sexual-napalm-2020-1|access-date=2021-09-16|website=Insider|language=en-US}}</ref> In response to a question about whether black women were interested in him, he said, "My dick is sort of like a white supremacist. I've got a Benetton heart and a fuckin' [[David Duke]] cock. I'm going to start dating separately from my dick."<ref name=Playboy>{{cite web|title=Playboy Interview: John Mayer|date=February 10, 2010|url=http://www.playboy.com/articles/playboy-interview-john-mayer|work=Playboy|access-date=February 10, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140831080718/http://www.playboy.com/articles/playboy-interview-john-mayer|archive-date=August 31, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> He also used the word "nigger" in the interview. This set off accusations in the media of him being a [[Misogyny|misogynist]], [[wikt:kiss-and-tell|kiss-and-tell]] ex-boyfriend, and [[Racism|racist]].<ref>Herrera, Monica (February 10, 2010). [https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/959433/john-mayers-sexually-racially-charged-playboy-interview-sparks-outrage "John Mayer's Sexually, Racially Charged Playboy Interview Sparks Outrage"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130219085115/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/959433/john-mayers-sexually-racially-charged-playboy-interview-sparks-outrage |date=February 19, 2013 }}. ''Billboard''. Retrieved February 10, 2010.</ref> He apologized via Twitter for his use of the word "nigger", saying, "It was arrogant of me to think I could intellectualize...a word that is so emotionally charged".<ref>Herrera, Monica (February 10, 2010), [https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/959424/john-mayer-apologizes-for-using-racial-slur-in-playboy-interview "Playboy Interview] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150705104645/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/959424/john-mayer-apologizes-for-using-racial-slur-in-playboy-interview |date=July 5, 2015 }}. ''Billboard''. Retrieved March 23, 2015.</ref> He also tearfully apologized to his band and fans at his concert in [[Nashville, Tennessee|Nashville]] later that night.<ref>{{cite AV media | date = February 10, 2010 | title = John Mayer Cries/Apologizes in Nashville, TN 10 February 2010 Sommet Center | medium = Concert footage |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x765IhCvnqg | access-date = March 19, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151017085446/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x765IhCvnqg | archive-date = October 17, 2015 | url-status=live }}</ref> In the following two years, he left New York and retreated from the media.<ref name=sniping/> Reflecting on that time in a May 2012 episode of ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'', he said, <blockquote>"I lost my head for a little while and I did a couple of dumb interviews and it kind of woke me up...It was a violent crash into being an adult. For a couple of years, it was just figuring it all out, and I'm glad I actually stayed out of the spotlight."<ref name="ellen">{{cite web|title=John Mayer on Taking a Break|url=http://ellen.warnerbros.com/2012/05/john_mayer_on_taking_a_break_0515.php|website=Warner Bros|access-date=June 12, 2012|date=May 15, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120617205210/http://ellen.warnerbros.com/2012/05/john_mayer_on_taking_a_break_0515.php|archive-date=June 17, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Chen|first=Joyce|title=John Mayer: 'I lost my head for a while'|url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2012-05-15/news/31714265_1_john-mayer-spotlight-interviews|work=Daily News|location=New York|access-date=June 12, 2012|date=May 15, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121028212158/http://articles.nydailynews.com/2012-05-15/news/31714265_1_john-mayer-spotlight-interviews|archive-date=October 28, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Koonse |first=Emma |title=John Mayer 'Lost His Head' 2 Years Ago |url=http://global.christianpost.com/news/john-mayer-lost-his-head-2-years-ago-75026/ |work=The Christian Post |access-date=June 12, 2012 |date=May 16, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130406091215/http://global.christianpost.com/news/john-mayer-lost-his-head-2-years-ago-75026/ |archive-date=April 6, 2013 }}</ref></blockquote>

Singer-songwriter [[Taylor Swift]] performed vocals for the song "[[Half of My Heart]]" on Mayer's November 2009 album ''[[Battle Studies (album)|Battle Studies]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Vena|first=Jocelyn|title=John Mayer Talks Taylor Swift Collaboration 'Half of My Heart'|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1625724/john-mayer-talks-taylor-swift-collaboration-half-my-heart.jhtml|website=MTV|access-date=June 11, 2012|date=November 6, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120414193121/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1625724/john-mayer-talks-taylor-swift-collaboration-half-my-heart.jhtml|archive-date=April 14, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> Rumors began to circulate in the media that the two were a couple, an assertion that neither addressed. However, Swift released a song called "[[Dear John (Taylor Swift song)|Dear John]]" in 2010, which was widely believed to be about her relationship with him. In June 2012, Mayer criticized the song, saying she never contacted him and that "it's abusing your talent to rub your hands together and go, 'Wait till he gets a load of this!'"<ref>{{cite magazine|title=John Mayer: Taylor Swift's 'Dear John' Song 'Humiliated Me'|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/john-mayer-taylor-swifts-dear-john-song-humiliated-me-20120606|magazine=Rolling Stone|access-date=June 6, 2012|date=June 11, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120623203359/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/john-mayer-taylor-swifts-dear-john-song-humiliated-me-20120606|archive-date=June 23, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> The song "Paper Doll" was reported to be a [[answer song|response]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/online/oscars/2013/06/taylor-swift-paper-doll-photos_slideshow_item0_1|title=Photos: Five Reasons to Think Taylor Swift Is John Mayer's "Paper Doll"|date=June 19, 2013|author=Julie Miller|magazine=Vanity Fair|access-date=August 9, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130806084246/http://www.vanityfair.com/online/oscars/2013/06/taylor-swift-paper-doll-photos_slideshow_item0_1|archive-date=August 6, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> In the March 21, 2019 episode of ''Current Mood'', however, Mayer said, <blockquote>"When 'Paper Doll' came out, 100% of the people believed it was about somebody...But the song was not about that person and I could never tell anybody, 'That's not true,' because then I would be breaking my rule that songwriters don't say who the songs are about or not about."<ref>{{cite AV media | people =JOhn Mayer | date =March 21, 2019 | title =Current Mood from Brisbane, Australia—John Mayer World Tour 2019 | medium =webshow | time =23m40s | location =Brisbane, Australia | publisher =Instagram }}</ref></blockquote>

In March 2014, Mayer sued watch dealer Robert Maron for $656,000 when he discovered that seven of the $5 million in watches he purchased from the dealer contained counterfeit parts.<ref>''People'' staff (March 29, 2014), "THE Action". ''Billboard''. '''126''' (11):3</ref><ref>James (March 20, 2014), [http://www.theversatilegent.com/the-horology-world-holds-its-breath-over-john-mayer-fake-watch-story/ "The Horology World Holds Its BreathOver John Mayer Fake Watch Story"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402181736/http://www.theversatilegent.com/the-horology-world-holds-its-breath-over-john-mayer-fake-watch-story/ |date=April 2, 2015 }}. Retrieved March 24, 2015.</ref> He dropped the action in May 2015, releasing a statement that asserted that research restored his "belief that Bob Maron is an expert on Rolex watches and confirmed that Bob Maron never sold him a counterfeit watch".<ref name="WOLF">{{cite web |last1=WOLF |first1=CAMERON |title=John Mayer Admits He Was Wrong About Potentially Fake $600,000 Rolex Collection |url=https://www.complex.com/style/2015/05/john-mayer-drops-fake-rolex-lawsuit |website=Complex |access-date=June 23, 2019 |language=en |date=May 21, 2015}}</ref>

